A spokesperson from Housing Works said that they had no idea who the man was when he dropped off the 'vandalized' painting last month.

'I don't know all the details, it was all done very secretively. But someone came in and dropped it off as an anonymous donation,' Housing Work's Rebecca Edmondson told The New York Post.

The thrift store was able to eventually find a buyer. They sold the painting to an anonymous individual who paid 'at least $450,000,' according to Gawker.

